Yagan Sasman is the fifth player to join Kaizer Chiefs in recent weeks. CAPE TOWN - Kaizer Chiefs have confirmed their fifth signing of the season. The Glamour Boys signed Yagan Sasman from Ajax Cape Town on a three-year contract. Sasman joins the Glamour Boys after spending the last 12 years in Cape Town. The 23-year-old defender can play at both left-back and centre-back positions. Sasman's signing comes after the Soweto based club welcomed four new players last earlier this month - Kearyn Baccus joined the club from Australian outfit Melbourne City, Serbian striker Samir NurkoviÄ‡, Ghanaian midfielder James Kotei and Zambian striker Lazarous Kambole. 